    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Christian Yelich** (72.61) as our premier play. While his base projection is solid, the combination of a favorable matchup against Littell and a strong dynamic platoon edge (+13%) makes him our highest-scoring asset despite a slightly neutral park factor. He is closely trailed by **Trea Turner** (71.43), whose elite speed profile and leadoff positioning against Gallen provide a high floor, and **Kyle Schwarber** (67.82), who benefits from a park boost and remains an engine for power in the #2 hole. **Caleb Durbin** (67.84) and **Colt Keith** (67.49) round out our top-tier targets; **Caleb Durbin** specifically benefits from an aggressive +10% boost due to wind direction, making him a critical start for stolen base production against a pitcher in Pallante who allows for decent opportunistic running.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical hurdles, most notably with **Yordan Alvarez** (55.60). Although he possesses an elite xwOBA, his score is severely depressed by a matchup against the formidable Logan Gilbert, whose SP_xERA of 2.86 is the lowest we face today. Despite the 19% penalty from the opposing skill level, his BvP history and lineup placement keep him active. On the bench, **Victor Scott II** (58.31) was the most difficult exclusion. While his speed profile is essential for our 5x5 objectives, his #9 position in the lineup creates a structural efficiency drag that left him just behind **Kazuma Okamoto** (58.71) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (61.24) in our final optimization. We remain cautious of **Hyeseong Kim**, who is benched today against the elite arm of deGrom, as his projection plummeted to 40.38 under the pressure of such a difficult matchup.",
